        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer29025341" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14227969061855032814">Prosperous people should feel guilty because there are homeless people in our cities. That is the main message in this Grisham novel. <br/><br/>In the book are perfectly normal people who become homeless because they are down on their luck. Strangely, no mention is made of the primary sources of homelessness: drugs and mental illness. No, according to The Street Lawyer, the problem of homlessness is caused by the selfish prosperity of our country.<br/><br/>Besides the misled preachiness of the story, it&apos;s also rath</span>
  <span id="freeText14227969061855032814" style="display:none">Prosperous people should feel guilty because there are homeless people in our cities. That is the main message in this Grisham novel. <br /><br />In the book are perfectly normal people who become homeless because they are down on their luck. Strangely, no mention is made of the primary sources of homelessness: drugs and mental illness. No, according to The Street Lawyer, the problem of homlessness is caused by the selfish prosperity of our country.<br /><br />Besides the misled preachiness of the story, it's also rather boring.</span>
